description.narrative: (Cambodia): Development Innovations brings together Cambodian civil society organizations and technologists to develop information and communications technology (ICT) solutions to address Cambodia's development challenges. A central feature of activity continues to be its ICT for development advisory services, which many individuals and organizations consider as the only neutral high-quality advice and technology referrals service available in the local market. With FY 2017 funds, the USG will continue to support Development Innovations to provide advisory services to help civil society organizations design, test, implement, and scale-up ICT solutions. The USG will ensure that Development Innovations can eventually transfer its advisory services to a local sustainable entity after the project ends. Throughout all of the activities that Development Innovations implements, the USG will continue to leverage partnerships and private sector engagement with civil society.
